article.headline: Furman 87, Chattanooga 78
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. -- Jordan Miller scored 31 points and Furman defeated Chattanooga 87-78 on Saturday night. Miller was 10 of 18 from the field and Amu Saaka, who finished with 19 points, was 7-for-11 for the Paladins (12-13, 6-8 Southern Conference). Furman, which snapped a two-game losing streak, shot 53.7 percent from the field (29 of 54). The Paladins trailed 25-21 with 2:41 left in the first half, and Saaka's three-point played pulled them within one with 2:28 to go until halftime. Furman tied it at 27-27 on Noah States' free throw with 42 seconds left in the first half. The Paladins then took the lead for good, 29-27, on Saaka's jumper, 39 seconds before halftime. Furman shot 63 percent in the second half (17 of 27), and led by as many as 16 with 10:02 remaining. DeAntre Jefferson scored 15 points, and Ricky Taylor and Keegan Bell added 14 each for the Mocs (13-14, 5-9).
